{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":29968,"record_hash":"sha256:2080d1af6c2da3a45135b746dc3b30c746abfb59bded468200e9b25d8cc10466","timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:23:08.144Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"assistant","text":"Yes, that is reasonable. If we decide consumers must sort anyway, then a GitMeta `set` becomes much more attractive.\n\nThe main caveat is what we put in the set.\n\nBad/simple-but-brittle version:\n\n```text\n:transcript = set<TranscriptRecord JSON>\n```\n\nThis dedupes only by exact JSON string. If the same raw record is captured later but our normalization/redaction shape changed slightly, GitMeta would store a second semantic duplicate.\n\nBetter version:\n\n```text\n:record-hashes = set<record_hash>\n:record:<record_hash> = TranscriptRecord JSON\n```\n\nThen the hash is the durable identity, and consumers read the hash set, load records, dedupe by construction, and sort by `source_key + record_index` or timestamp.\n\nThat shape is semantically cleaner than `list + record-hashes`:\n\n```text\ncurrent:\n  :transcript = list<record>\n  :record-hashes = set<hash>\n\nmore canonical:\n  :records = set<hash>\n  :record:<hash> = record\n```\n\nThe downside is more GitMeta keys and slightly more code. But it may actually remove conceptual weirdness: no append-only list pretending to be canonical order, no separate dedupe index for a list that can still contain duplicates, and no future reader needing to distrust list order.\n\nFor the POC, I’d frame it this way:\n\n- If we care mostly about “append transcript timeline locally,” list plus set is fine.\n- If we care about future handoff/materialize/merge/review readers, `set<hash> + record:<hash>` is probably the better data model.\n\nGiven where the feature is heading, I think your instinct is right. The set-based shape is likely more honest. It says: “these are the records we know about; readers decide presentation order from record fields.”","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:23:08.144Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}